deck: Nicole must choose between Johnny or Peter.
description: Nicole must choose between remaining in Johnny's arms, or leaving him for Peter.
name: Moment Of Truth!

description: Bob falls for a woman with a secret.
name: Don't Let Her Fool You!

description:
Summertime is quickly coming to an end and Archie realizes that he has not filled his quota of summer dating before the school year starts. This leads to a number of rushed dates (with all different girls) with hilarity ensuing at every turn - especially when the friends of Betty Cooper turn Archie's plan against him. Guest-starring Ginger Snapp, Suzie, Linda Lake, Laurie Moore and Toni Topaz - and Archie's dog, Vegas!

List of covers and their creators:

RegRegular CoverDan Parent1
Var"Veronica" Pin-Up Variant CoverDan Decarlo2
Var"Betty" Pin-Up Variant CoverDan Decarlo3

Note: The digital edition (7/30/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Dating Drama!

description:
The fifth volume of Archie's highly acclaimed graphic novel series features celebrated writer Paul Kupperberg's tight-knit ongoing romantic storyline of Archie as a young newlywed in two very different universes, one where he marries wealthy socialite Veronica Lodge and the other where he marries girl-next-door Betty Cooper. This volume follows Betty and Reggie's time in the reality TV spotlight, and Cheryl Blossom continues her fight against breast cancer, while also inspiring women struggling to do the same! Plus all the romantic ups and downs that Riverdale is famous for! Archie: The Married Life Book 5 collects issues 25-30 of the Eisner-nominated Life With Archie magazine.

Note: The digital edition (7/30/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Book Five

description: Low on supplies and weapons, Thanatos and Dinah make their way to downtown Savannah to stock up on their way back to Thanatos' house. Once they reach downtown they realize they're right at the heart of the zombie invasion!

As Victor and Ivan struggle with their experimentations, an equally macabre series of events take place across the street at the town's funeral home. Operated by the enigmatic owner known simply as Leland, the questionable undertaker's expansive property houses more than it appears.

The Tussle at Tenochtitlan!

Bunyan faces insurmountable odds and barely-surmountable stairs on his path to the top! It's high-flying action in the Living Ring of Tenochtitlan!
name: The Tussle at Tenochtitlan!

description:
Blasto and Naomi are on the trail of Teeth Waters, hoping he can lead them to his escaped con brother Harry. Little do they know Harry is trapped in the basement of the haunted house Richard has led his friends to.

Calling to the children one by one Harry seems to become a conduit, speaking through many voices and telling many different stories. Now the biggest question is why he doesn't seem to notice that strange glowing rock that's punctured his shoulder.

The wacky antics of Boots and Pup continue in issue #2! This time around in "Caddy Slack" Boots spends an exhausting first day on the job only to find an unexpected dinner guest! Meanwhile Pup finds a new friend in "Night of the Cabbage Creeps!"

Boots on the Ground.

Heels is dropped off in 1816 where she meets up with Sergeant 'Murica. The two then go on a hunt through zombie infested jungles for the lost city of El Dorado. Meanwhile, Boots has to act fast to keep the Clawed-Agent from dying in 2016.
name: Boots On the Ground.

description: Doug and Gavin escort Magnus to meet with the vampires in a desperate gambit to save Lucy's life.

Death of a Nation - Part 3

Can the newly united Harriet Tubman, Johnny Appleseed and U.S. Grant survive their first test...protecting the fragile body of Abraham Lincoln. The Civil Four battle The Dandy's arcane army as the President fights to stay alive. Can The Spirit of Ben Franklin bring him back or will he push him further over the edge?
name: Death of A Nation Part 3

description:
Everybody knows the brontosaurs, but what about the mamenchisaurus? The third chapter in the DINOSAURS saga delves deeper into the world of these fearsome lizards, exploring rarely discussed creatures like the cryolophosaurus, taking a look at the spines of the stegosaurus, and asking important questions like "What happened when a dinosaur had a toothache?"

DINOSAURS is your guided tour through the rough-and-tumble world of the mightiest beasts to ever walk the earth!

Note: The digital edition (7/30/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Jurassic Smarts

description:
Children of the Grave

Berenn meets the dryads as he looks for answers regarding the danger lurking the outskirts of the forest. Amorphis and Wind see the conflict once again gets near them. And we get to know a little bit about Amorphis past!
name: Children of the Grave

description:
Tales Of Rewind

They're still making these?! YES! Back after much critical acclaim, apparently it's Freestyle time! The comic no-one thought would make it past the first issue yet here it is at number 08! Created by Australian Mark Pursell who likes to think he can draw and write and stuff and occasionally can, Freestyle is a comic. It is funny and has words and pretty pictures!

This time around, Stupid receives a strange package containing something he has never seen before, a video cassette tape. This tape is no ordinary tape though. It is magical and causes catastrophic events to happen. His friends dissapear and are replaced by some of the earliest characters created for the Freestyle universe, Mr Fishy and Norman.

As you would expect, it's just another badly thought out plot by Chloe. Sigh.
name: Tales Of Rewind

description:
Gabe's investigation into Professor Kreel's lab turns up more than he bargained for...

As he attempts to seek answers to the kidnapping and smuggling of the people in the truck, Gabe is thrown into the path of a mysterious organisation who will do anything to keep their secrets.

Issue #2 represents an action packed follow up to the introductory tale told in the first book.

A tale about the collapse of government, the rise of corporate power and the dwindling value of traditional morality in a futuristic Melbourne City.

Strangers at Doors

As the day comes to an end, Captain Sanders finds consolation in his role as a father, not yet facing a future as a civilian. He has no idea what is about to enter into his family life.

A bloody horror is discovered on the ranch of Theo Soell, and an autopsy is abruptly interrupted to the surprise of Dr. Regina Coulter.

And, through it all, Dr. Henry Pratt must accelerate his experiments with the amoeba...
name: Strangers At Doors

description:
Here Be Dragons

In which our heroes run afoul of demons and communal bathing.
name: Here Be Dragons

description:
The Wolves of Barra

After slaying the Sea Serpent of Castlebay and being denied their just reward, the HEAD LOPPER, Norgal, and his companion, the head of Agatha Blue Witch, have fallen on hard times. To make matters worse, the demigod of Barra plots against them, sending his Wolves to do his bidding. The HEAD LOPPER's blade runs red with blood once more.
name: The Wolves of Barra

description:
Theme Park Mascots of Doom

When a brand new candy bar, called Snakatak, starts turning people into zombies in the small town of Sweetooth, it is up to Clea Brown and her ragtag group to stop the evil Yumzy Corporation from raining down the Sugarpocalypse. Issue 3 explodes with the opening of Yumzyland, the treat themed amusement park! The mass release of Snakataks is imminent. Can the team undermine Yumzy in time to save the park patrons, and avert candicide?
name: Theme Park Mascots of Doom

description: The White Warrior has to confront again The Defacer - a dark God who is thirsty for death. This enemy is too strong for our hero, he is severely injured and no help is seen around. The Defacer's plan is going well so far but even he is not conscious enough to foresee all the consequences of his terrible act... A consequence that will reverse the course of events for him and The White Warrior and Siddhartha and everyone on Earth!
name: The Growth of Light Within

description:
Homeland Insecurity IV

In "Johnny Saturn: Homeland Insecurity" part IV, the government imposes a new order on the Squadron Premiere, and a new leader, Titanium Tom, a soldier who boasts of a new era for Spire City's metaheroes. Titanium Tom's leadership leaves a lot to be desired, and it's up to the Utopian to teach Tom a lesson in manners! Also, Mollie, the escaped cyborgs, shows us what she is made of--literally. This edition of "Johnny Saturn" has 24 pages of comics, two characters' Who's Who pages, one Spire City map, one pinup, and six bonus sketchbook pages, all for 37 pages of content!
name: Homeland Insecurity IV

description:
The Refugees, Mala and Thane, have lived for the past fourteen years in the sanctuary city of Chuh Nar with their adopted son Pale.

Naive to the civil war raging outside the city walls, Pale has had a relatively care free life.

Our story continues when two assailants breach the city defenses, attempting to abduct Pale and bring him before Baron Kah Lee for questioning.
name: Rise of the Ape King Chapter Two

description: Brand has been stunned by some unwanted truths. Will this stop his mission to put an end to Lord's brutal reign?

Seeking Samarkand Part 8 of 8

THE FINAL CHAPTER!

Every question, every mystery, every circumstance brought the Lost Kids to Samarkand and it's finally time to learn the truth behind the Deors!

...and maybe finally go home...?
name: Seeking Samarkand Part 8 of 8

description:
Love the Sinner but Hate the Sin

Lower East Side Story #4 features the next chapter which takes place in New York in the 1980s, a city at the brink of bankruptcy and total collapse.

Dwight returns from his stint on Rikers, to find a neighborhood in the midst of a massive transformation courtesy of a new destructive force: crack.

His relationship deepens with Carrie and evolves with Tony. Meanwhile, Skin becomes one of the early and unforseen recipients of an era-defining event.
name: Love the Sinner But Hate the Sin

description: Each issue of Marvel Previews is a comic book-sized, 120-page, full-color guide and preview to all of Marvel's upcoming releases - it's your #1 source for advanced information on Marvel Comics! This August issue features items scheduled to ship in October 2014 and beyond.

Heavy Metal Parking Lot?!

Nothing is simple for Nick and Lou anymore; all they want to do on a Friday night is rock out at a heavy metal show. But when Nick's waylaid by a tough guy who seems to know something about Nick's missing parents, the evening takes a turn for the worst...and the more mysterious. Who or what do all the villains have in common? And where does this new pink-hair stranger fit in?
name: Heavy Metal Parking Lot?!

description:
Welcome to Midnight, prt.2

Something strange is going on at Midnight Collectables. People are found passed out with marks on their necks and Romero's customers are jumping to wild conclusions. Shawn refuses to believe his new friend is responsible and is determined to get to the bottom of the strange event. But when he finds the truth, he'll learn Romero does have a few secrets he's kept from Shawn...
name: Welcome to Midnight, prt.2

description:
MIND MGMT concludes its second year in this crucial one-shot revealing “The Life and Times of Henry Lyme,” with a shocking twist that sets up the final two arcs!

The AV Club’s best series of 2013!

This issue is the perfect jumping-on point for new readers!

Retailers, see your order form for a special offer.
name: The Life and Times of Henry Lyme

description: After a chance encounter at sea, fisherman Mishka washes ashore on an uncharted island. Surrounded by monsters and worse, can Mishka survive long enough to solve the mystery of the Sea Devil and return home? Join her, Captain Furball, and Admiral Ghost on the adventure of their lives!

In Chapter 2, Ariel battles at pack of vicious Daemons on her own, Michael tells the story of his first encounter with Lucifer, and Remiel discovers a different side to the monsters they've been fighting.

Who is "He?" The skillful young man who set the top three killers in Zero's organization against each other comes to their rescue, but to what end? Who does he work for? And what is his baffling agenda? Only an unholy alliance between former foes can lead to answers...

Cue the Strings

It's field trip time at Kitty Country Day! Gobi, the four-time national champion string cat, is coming to town to promote exercise and play with the national cat pastime. With tryouts for the school string team on their way, the Scouts' excitement is at a fever pitch. But will the most thrilling day of Pimper's life be ruined by a challenge from a rival Panther Scouts pack?
name: Cue the Strings

description:
The Detachment Bell

Penny Palabras, 17, is being tormented by the Straw Man. It seems that he's burned the library to the ground, ghosting the Librarian. Penny has her potential Ghost Accomplice, but she's surprised when a Tiger Devil is waiting for her in the darkness, offering help. Penny knows that devils are manipulative and can't be trusted, but her nightmares won't let her sleep, her friends and family can't understand, and the Straw Man is getting more powerful every day.
name: The Detachment Bell

description:
Forbidden Lore

Corvan Moore enters the spirit realm a second time. This time he intends to explore the potential of his new-found ability. Corvan is determined to hold on to life in order to seek revenge against his enemies, but doing so may strip him of what's left of his humanity.
name: Forbidden Lore

description:
Hellucination

In a turn of fate, Death will tumble down into his own personal Hell.
name: Hellucination

description:
Back in the Game

While in Russia searching for Gabriel Evans Girard, his boss at the Justice International detective agency, Rob uncovers a plot by a disaffected Russian army officer to sell a suitcase nuclear device on the international black market.
name: Back In the Game

description:
Mars Gambit

With Raamon now an ally, Sage focuses on completing her goal of solving the galactic media cover up. From the claustrophobic stand-off in the Trader's ship to the spacious Cray mansion, Sage charges towards the truth. Imogen and Soo Mi realize the level of contempt that Elvis Cray holds their relationship in. And with Groth closing in, Mars Gambit rip roars into a spiral of events that will change the course of human history.
name: Mars Gambit

description: The Sentinels battle with Damien concludes as the fate of one of their members is revealed and changes the team forever!

Throughout the decades, The Shadow has served as a timeless agent of justice, bringing death and disaster to tyrants and criminals alike. During the decadent 1980s, this mysterious Master of Men faced perhaps his deadliest opponents yet: the Seven Deadly Finns, a crime family gripping New York City in a stranglehold. When The Shadow's network of agents applies pressure to their vast operations, the Finn brothers push back, enlisting serial killers and terrorists into their ranks. The violence escalates, leading to an explosive confrontation atop the Empire State Building and a shock ending which no one - not even The Shadow - could know!"
name: The Seven Deadly Finns - Part 3: Fool's Parade

description:
Chapter 4 pt 5

The big showdown between Seth and Suryu to save the whole team.
name: Wild Things Part 5

description:
Cost Of Living

In three new tales, The Trench Coat Samurai finds himself in situations that are not all that they seem to be.
name: Cost Of Living

description: Tyler and Alexander have found Katherine's hiding place, but they'll have to get through an Expression witch before they can destroy her!
name: Loyal Dogs Part 3 of 3

description:
...when the bow breaks...

Previously in Velica, our hero was slowed down in her tracks by a group of masked men called The Dominion. After escaping their clutches, Velica is now focused on her next target, Club Columbo, which is one of Domino's pet projects. Domino has commissioned his trusted right hand man, Syxx Jones, to personally oversee the retrieval of his lost fortune. Unbeknowest to Syxx, Velica is already there waiting for him.

Tempers are flaring around Zombillenium, the monster amusement park run by monsters. When one hires only the dead (or witches!) in a region where unemployment is in the double digits, one must expect some friction. But things get particularly ugly when the park's security is breached from two sides: activists and a very strange visitor, mom to two peculiar sons the head of the park seems to remember from somewhere... Gretchen and Aurelian do their best to help save a precarious explosive situation! All presented in De Pins' trademark tongue-in-cheek jubilant black humor and stunning art.

Note: The digital edition (7/30/2014) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Human Resources

description:
Society as a Hole

Our hero(?) Zukah finds some direction to his efforts to join Earthling society when he teams up with siblings Darius and Daphne as they try to deal with dangerous visitors from another world!
name: Society As A Hole

volume.name: Rusty och hans vän Rin Tin Tin
